source: crates/hsh-cli/tests/snapshots.rs
expression: stdout
snapshot_kind: text
---
Hash a password and print the storable form to stdout

Usage: hsh hash [OPTIONS]

Options:
      --json
          Emit machine-readable JSON instead of plain text

      --policy <POLICY>
          Preset policy to apply. Defaults to OWASP-2025
          
          [default: owasp]

          Possible values:
          - owasp:   OWASP-2025 minimum (Argon2id, m=19456, t=2, p=1)
          - rfc9106: RFC 9106 §4 first-recommended (Argon2id, m=2^21, t=1, p=4)
          - fips:    Hardened FIPS profile (PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA-256, 600k iters,
            Backend::Fips140Required — requires a FIPS-capable build)

  -a, --algorithm <ALGORITHM>
          Override the primary algorithm

          Possible values:
          - argon2id: Argon2id — recommended default
          - argon2i:  Argon2i — verify-only for legacy hashes
          - argon2d:  Argon2d — exposed for completeness
          - bcrypt:   Bcrypt — Blowfish-based KDF
          - scrypt:   Scrypt — memory-hard KDF
          - pbkdf2:   PBKDF2-HMAC-SHA-256 — the only FIPS-validated path

      --password <PASSWORD>
          Password (insecure: leaves password in shell history). Omit and provide via stdin or
          `$HSH_PASSWORD` instead
          
          [env: HSH_PASSWORD]

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
